Temporal.ETAS.fit.Rd

Fits the remporal ETAS model and returns the results. This function decomposes the input.list for the `Hawkes.bru2`` function.

Usage

Temporal.ETAS.fit(input.list)

Arguments

input.list

All input data and parameters are passed to inlabru via this structured list. This is the output of the function create_input_list_temporal_withCatalogue or create_input_list_temporal_noCatalogue

Value

The fitted model as a bru object, which is a list
